&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;145&quot; data-end=&quot;163&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;149&quot; data-end=&quot;161&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;164&quot; data-end=&quot;551&quot;&gt;At &lt;strong data-start=&quot;167&quot; data-end=&quot;187&quot;&gt;The Pharmacy Hub&lt;/strong&gt;, we collaborate with &lt;strong data-start=&quot;209&quot; data-end=&quot;314&quot;&gt;pharmaceutical brands, manufacturers, health brands, telemedicine providers, and healthcare companies&lt;/strong&gt; to deliver essential products &lt;strong data-start=&quot;345&quot; data-end=&quot;370&quot;&gt;directly to patients.&lt;/strong&gt; Our expertise allows us to seamlessly distribute &lt;strong data-start=&quot;420&quot; data-end=&quot;487&quot;&gt;pharmaceuticals, medical devices, and other healthcare products&lt;/strong&gt; to consumers, ensuring greater accessibility and convenience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a knowledgeable and detail-oriented &lt;strong&gt;Non-Sterile &amp;amp; Hazardous Compounding Pharmacy Technician&lt;/strong&gt; to join our compounding team. This role involves the accurate preparation of both non-hazardous and hazardous compounded medications, including &lt;strong&gt;troches, creams, ointments, gels, nasal sprays, oral solutions and suspensions and rapid dissolve tablets (RDTs)&lt;/strong&gt;. The technician must be proficient in USP &amp;lt;795&amp;gt; and &amp;lt;800&amp;gt; standards and capable of working in accordance with safety protocols and pharmacy regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compounding Preparation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately compound customized non-sterile medications based on master formulation records.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare a variety of dosage forms including troches, creams, ointments, gels, nasal sprays, oral drops, solutions, suspensions, and Rapid Dissolve Tablets (RDTs).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle and compound hazardous drugs (HDs) in compliance with USP &amp;lt;800&amp;gt; guidelines.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform cleaning, decontamination, and garbing procedures in designated non-sterile hazardous areas.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clean and organized compounding workspaces, adhering to cross-contamination prevention protocols.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately document all compounding processes and batch records.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate and maintain compounding equipment such as balances, homogenizers, and mixers.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with the pharmacist and QA team to ensure batch accuracy and quality control.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in inventory control and proper storage and labeling of raw materials, hazardous components, and finished products.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in internal audits and training updates to stay current with USP and OSHA regulations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality Control&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality checks at each stage of the compounding process to verify dosage accuracy and product integrity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all regulatory and safety guidelines, including USP &amp;lt;795&amp;gt; for non-sterile compounding and USP &amp;lt;800&amp;gt; for hazardous drug compounding.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record all compounding activities in accordance with pharmacy policies and regulatory standards.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailed logs of ingredient batches, expiration dates, and patient-specific information.&lt

