&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;145&quot; data-end=&quot;163&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;149&quot; data-end=&quot;161&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;164&quot; data-end=&quot;551&quot;&gt;At &lt;strong data-start=&quot;167&quot; data-end=&quot;187&quot;&gt;The Pharmacy Hub&lt;/strong&gt;, we collaborate with &lt;strong data-start=&quot;209&quot; data-end=&quot;314&quot;&gt;pharmaceutical brands, manufacturers, health brands, telemedicine providers, and healthcare companies&lt;/strong&gt; to deliver essential products &lt;strong data-start=&quot;345&quot; data-end=&quot;370&quot;&gt;directly to patients.&lt;/strong&gt; Our expertise allows us to seamlessly distribute &lt;strong data-start=&quot;420&quot; data-end=&quot;487&quot;&gt;pharmaceuticals, medical devices, and other healthcare products&lt;/strong&gt; to consumers, ensuring greater accessibility and convenience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Job description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The HR Generalist serves as a key people partner to operational leadership at The Pharmacy Hub, supporting a mission-driven, high-growth organization dedicated to breaking barriers in healthcare by championing access, intervention, and affordability. This role manages the full employee lifecycle—from recruitment to offboarding—while ensuring compliance with employment laws, pharmacy regulations, and internal policies. Overseeing core HR functions, including onboarding, employee relations, benefits, performance management, and compliance, the HR Generalist partners with employees and leaders to promote consistent practices, support collaboration, and foster a positive, compliant workplace aligned with organizational goals. Success in this role requires strong communication, problem-solving skills, and a commitment to customer focus, innovation, and continuous improvement. Success in this role requires strong communication, problem-solving skills, and knowledge of employment laws, all guided by our commitment to a customer- first mindset, innovation for intervention and continuous improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talent Acquisition &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage full-cycle recruitment for hourly, technical, and professional roles&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with department heads to draft and post position requisitions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Screen, interview, and coordinate offers in compliance with EEO guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain applicant tracking system (ATS) and hiring metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Onboarding &amp;amp; Offboarding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute pre-employment background checks and drug screening per DEA/pharmacy standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate new hire orientation including HIPAA training and compliance acknowledgments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage separation process, conduct exit interviews, and process documentation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Relations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as first point of contact for employee concerns and conflict resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support management in performance improvement plans (PIPs) and disciplinary actions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Policy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure adherence to federal and state employment law (FLSA, FMLA, ADA, OSHA)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain employee files and records in compliance with HIPAA and state pharmacy board requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer DEA background check compliance for roles with controlled substance access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Training &amp;amp; Development&lt;/stron

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;145&quot; data-end=&quot;163&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;149&quot; data-end=&quot;161&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;164&quot; data-end=&quot;551&quot;&gt;At &lt;strong data-start=&quot;167&quot; data-end=&quot;187&quot;&gt;The Pharmacy Hub&lt;/strong&gt;, we collaborate with &lt;strong data-start=&quot;209&quot; data-end=&quot;314&quot;&gt;pharmaceutical brands, manufacturers, health brands, telemedicine providers, and healthcare companies&lt;/strong&gt; to deliver essential products &lt;strong data-start=&quot;345&quot; data-end=&quot;370&quot;&gt;directly to patients.&lt;/strong&gt; Our expertise allows us to seamlessly distribute &lt;strong data-start=&quot;420&quot; data-end=&quot;487&quot;&gt;pharmaceuticals, medical devices, and other healthcare products&lt;/strong&gt; to consumers, ensuring greater accessibility and convenience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Inventory Clerk plays an essential role in maintaining the accuracy and organization of our inventory operations. This position is responsible for conducting physical counts, recording stock movements, supporting replenishment activities, and ensuring inventory records are up to date in our systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports directly to the Inventory Supervisor, who will provide onboarding, day-to-day guidance, performance tracking, and goal setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity for someone who is detail-oriented, reliable, and eager to grow within a fast-paced supply chain environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;Inventory Counting &amp;amp; Physical Verification&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine cycle counts, spot checks, and scheduled physical inventory audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record count results accurately in the inventory management system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and report discrepancies between physical counts and system records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure items are properly organized and accessible for counting events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supply required raw materials to the production team as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory Data Entry &amp;amp; Record Keeping&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter and update inventory transactions including receipts, transfers, and adjustments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate item records such as locations, quantities, and unit of measure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process inventory adjustment transactions following established approval procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure documentation is complete and filed appropriately for each transaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Replenishment Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor stock levels and flag items that have reached reorder points.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in generating purchase or replenishment requests under supervisor guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify incoming shipments against purchase orders and report discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support receiving and put-away processes to maintain organized storage areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discrepancy Reporting &amp;amp; Basic Reconciliation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report inventory variances to the Inventory Supervisor with supporting documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in researching variances by reviewing receiving logs and transaction records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help coordinate with warehouse staff to investigate and correct count errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;145&quot; data-end=&quot;163&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;149&quot; data-end=&quot;161&quot;&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;164&quot; data-end=&quot;551&quot;&gt;At &lt;strong data-start=&quot;167&quot; data-end=&quot;187&quot;&gt;The Pharmacy Hub&lt;/strong&gt;, we collaborate with &lt;strong data-start=&quot;209&quot; data-end=&quot;314&quot;&gt;pharmaceutical brands, manufacturers, health brands, telemedicine providers, and healthcare companies&lt;/strong&gt; to deliver essential products &lt;strong data-start=&quot;345&quot; data-end=&quot;370&quot;&gt;directly to patients.&lt;/strong&gt; Our expertise allows us to seamlessly distribute &lt;strong data-start=&quot;420&quot; data-end=&quot;487&quot;&gt;pharmaceuticals, medical devices, and other healthcare products&lt;/strong&gt; to consumers, ensuring greater accessibility and convenience.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build the operating system for patient-centric care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bond OS is the platform layer for modern care delivery. It connects structured patient intake, longitudinal patient context, provider review, clinic and admin operations, orders, prescriptions, commerce rails, platform APIs, analytics, support workflows, and applied AI/ML into one coherent system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthcare delivery is usually fragmented: intake in one place, clinical review in another, ordering and prescription status somewhere else, operations in spreadsheets, support in tickets, and analytics after the fact. Bond OS is built to make those flows work together: one patient context, clear workflows for every role, durable platform primitives, and intelligent assistance where it improves speed, quality, and safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Product Lead to own the roadmap for Bond OS across product surfaces and platform primitives. This is a senior, hands-on product leadership role for someone who can move between client conversations, patient and provider workflows, technical contracts, data models, operational edge cases, AI/ML release discipline, and crisp execution with engineering and design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role matters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bond OS is entering a new chapter. The core platform is live, the product surface area is expanding, and the opportunity is to make the system more unified, more patient-centric, more operationally powerful, and more intelligent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will shape how the platform scales: how intake becomes usable clinical context, how providers and clinic teams move through work, how orders and prescriptions are tracked, how clients understand performance, how APIs and permissions become stronger platform primitives, and how applied AI/ML earns its way into high-consequence workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The mandate is clear: turn a powerful care-delivery platform into a sharper operating system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bond OS roadmap&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own the product roadmap across the full platform:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patient intake, patient portal, and longitudinal patient context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provider workflows, review queues, clinical decisioning, and safety review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clinic and admin operations, group management, permissions, and oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orders, prescriptions, catalog, commerce, payments, promotions, and fulfillment handoffs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Platform APIs, integrations, auditability, data contracts, and status models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytics for operations, outcomes, quality, and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Applied AI/ML across intake, summarization, triage, drafting, operations, and decision-support context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will set priorities,

